      "content": "but an anchor also drags things down to the bottom. that's what i am. i'm not helping them grow, i'm just weighing them down and making it harder for them to swim. i look at how much more peaceful and calm they would be if they didn't have to worry about me or my constant mistakes. it feels like i'm just causing them endless trauma. isn't it more compassionate to just step away and let them heal in peace? if i stayed, i'd just keep hurting them. it feels like the most loving thing i could possibly do is just give them that space.",
